All seems to be ready for the new kind of fuel, but no large orders can be delivered until the pipe which is to convey the naphtha from Baku to Batoum has been completed.

abstract: TALEQUAH, Indian Territory, April 10.--The Cherokee Female Seminary situated one mile from here, burned down at noon to-day and the loss is $250,000. The seminary was built in 1858 and was intended to accommodate 200 girls. It cost originally $150,000, but a few years ago an addition costing $80,000 was erected. No lives were lost, but the loss is the greatest ever experienced by the Cherokees.

abstract: CHICAGO, Ill., April 11.--Mrs. Marie Dalvi, an Italian, 30 years of age, living at 87 Austin-avenue, was fatally stabbed by her husband Nicolai Dalvi, last evening. A bad wound was also inflicted in her right arm. Dalvi was immediately arrested.

abstract: HARRISONBURG, Va., April 27.--A freight train going north on the Valley Branch of the Baltimore and Ohio Railroad was wrecked near Timberville Station about 1 o'clock to-day. Billey Cooley, of Strasburg, Va., a brakeman, was killed and Edward Russell, conductor, was badly hurt. There were seven passengers on the train, but they were not hurt. Three cars were demolished. The cause of the accident is unknown, the engine having kept the track.
